You know how people 
have these little habits 
That get you down. Like Bernie. 
Bernie like to chew gum. 
No, not chew. POP. So I came home this one day, 
And I am really irritated, and 
looking for a little sympathy 
and there's Bernie layin' 
on the couch, drinkin' a beer 
and chewin'. No, not chewin'. 
Poppin'. So, I said to him, 
I said, "You pop that 
gum one more time..." 
and he did. 
So I took the shotgun off the wall 
and I fired two warning shots... 
...into his head. 


[ANNIE (Spoken)] 
I met Ezekiel Young from 
Salt Lake city about two years ago 
and he told me he was single 
and we hit it off right away. 
So, we started living together. 
He'd go to work, he'd come home, I'd 
fix him a drink, We'd have dinner. 
And then I found out, 
"Single" he told me? 
Single, my ass. Not only 
was he married 
...oh, no, he had six wives. 
One of those Mormons, you know. So that 
night, when he came home, I fixed him 
his drink as usual. 
You know, some guys just can't hold 
their arsenic. 

 JUNE (Spoken)] 
Now, I'm standing in the kitchen 
carvin' up the chicken for dinner, 
minding my own business, 
and in storms my husband Wilbur, 
in a jealous rage. 
"You been screwin' the milkman," 
he says. He was crazy 
and he kept screamin', 
"you been screwin the milkman." 
And then he ran into my knife. 
He ran into my knife ten times! 

[ALL] 
If you'd have been there 
If you'd have seen it 
I betcha you would have done the same! 

VELMA] 
My sister, Veronica and 
I did this double act 
and my husband, Charlie, 
used to travel round with us. 
Now, for the last number in our act, 
we did these 20 acrobatic tricks in a row 
One,two,three,four,five...splits, spread eagles, 
back flips,flip flops, one right after the other. 
So this one night before the show we're down at the hotel Cicero,the three of us,boozin', havin' a few laughs and 
we ran out of ice, so I go out to get some. 
I come back, open the door, and there's Veronica and 
Charlie doing Number Seventeen the spread eagle. 
Well, I was in such a state of shock, 
I completely blacked out. I can't remember a thing. 
It wasn't until later, 
when I was washing the blood off my hands 
I even knew they were dead. 

[MONA(Spoken)] 
I loved Al Lipschitz 
more than I can possibly say. 
He was a real artistic guy... 
sensitive... a painter. 
But he was always trying 
to find himself. 
He'd go out every night 
looking for himself 
and on the way 
he found Ruth, 
Gladys, 
Rosemary and Irving. 
I guess you can say we broke 
up because of artistic differences. 
He saw himself as alive 
and I saw him dead.

It was so funny....too bad noone brought a camera. But besides the fact that it is a fun place, the food and drinks are awesome.

So now the crappy news..starting monday I am going to a new room at work. YUCK...it was bad enough when it was one day, now it is for good. Where do I start? It's been awhile since I have written. 

Lets see...So I have ringworm...how hot is that? Haha...but because of it I can't work in a mouse room...so  lost all my overtime I was going to get, then yesterday I was trying to go to work to get my leg looked at and my car was acting funny, I checked the oil and the transmission fluid, and all was well. So I decided to try driving it to the video store and later to the food mart and it was fine, so this morning I went to go to work and it wouldn't even start, and when I was turning the key the windshield wipers started going..even though they weren't on..weird. So there goes some more money..then I got a ride with Travis and get to work and they said my leg is not healed enough I have to go home...and of course I couldn't get shawns keys until 9:30, so I had to sit around, then I have to go pick him up and go with him to ellsworth. yuck. 

It wouldn't be so bad if we weren't trying to save up for an apartment. I got accepted at Northeast tech to go back to school, but because of traveling so far, we decided to get an apartment. We'll see when it finally happens...oh and I have to find a co-signer before I can go to school...ya..real nice..don't know anybody. It just seems like nothing can go right. It seems like there is always a wall in the way. 

Went out a few weekends ago for my friend Amanda's 21st B-day. That was fun, went to Margarita's then stayed at the Ramada and went down to Barnaby's. Had Jolly Rancher shooters...OMG...the best shit I have ever had. I had 4 in maybe an hour..whoa, I was drunk. I even got up and danced. and when I went to work the next week some guy asked if that was me there...it was so embarrassing, I figured noone from work would see me...o'well. 

Well for now I guess thats all that is really going on..hopfully I can get overtime this week, but because I used vaca. time to make up for today, i have a feeling any extra hours will either take over my vaca. hours, or just be straight overtime..which is a waste of my time..yah..can't ANYTHING just go right for once. Mom said it's the Carroll curse and I need to get married to Shawn so my luck will change. LOL...we'll see if that ever happens....

So, I have decided to take this weekend to relax and do NOTHING. Just sleep, get some sun, maybe read a book. Who knows...but I am hoping for a stress free relaxing weekend...we'll see if it happens. I've just been so tired and down and need a little break. Can't wait for my vacation August 22-26...yah...
So I won't be seeing my parents this weekend...kinda bummed about that. Miss them..and now all I do is worry that if I don't make it down then dad will have another heart attack and maybe he wont make it this time. I feel so guilty bout everything and everyone all the time and it just stresses me out. I need this weekend before I make myself sick. I think Sunday I am going to the beach with Travis, Amie, and Shawn. I hope so, that would be fun..yet still relaxing. 

So last Friday Shawn, Travis and I went out. We went to the Dry Dock to eat supper, then to Cyclones for drinks. I had Blue Hawaiians...OMG..so good, and I got really drunk. I ended up calling Reanna at like midnight or so...oops..she didn't answer though ;-( probably a good thing. Hahahaha. Then I called my parents and talked to my dad..haha..poor guy. I woke him up ;-(

A few weekends ago Shawn and I met mom and dad over to Les and Dianes, and Christy was there and we all were drinking, and everyone there go drunk. Les threw Christy in the pool in her clothes so she had to wear mine. Then he threw her in again, so I had to give her more clothes, that she spilt coffee brandy all over. Then her an mom were singing Karaoke (sp?) That was a sight to see. Dad was drunk and dancing, I was happy to see him happy, although I don't think he should be drinking..but ya know...at least he isn't smoking. 

Well I guess thats it. Gonna go do..someting...don't know...Shawn wants me to play Halo..and I did promise...but he's playing with a bunch of people I don't know which makes me uncomfortable. So we'll see...i am sure you all care..lol...

Well its 10:02 in the morning and Shawn is still in bed, and I am here showered and ready to go...for the most part. I ache all over, my h ead, my body..and its been like that every morning for like 3 weeks. It sucks. I don't know why. Also my mood has been off the wall...pissed one second, sad and depressed the next minute, and then happy and horny...and i mean..like off the walls happy and horny..extremely..its weird. Even Ericka at work said I wasn't acting like myself the other day, when i was sad, then yesterday you couldn't get me to shut up and I was so giddy..the thing is, I really don't feel like myself. I don't know why. Me and Shawn are doing great. No problems there. So i don't know. well i guess thats it for now cause Shawn is getting up now and we are going to my parents for the night. See you all later.

So just a quick note....make sure when you are living with your boyfriends family...you double check after your shower that you have picked up all of your clothes off the bathroom floor... last night Travis comes in and says "jenn, i think you left your undies on the bathroom floor" and sure enough there they were in the middle of the floor..and i know someone had to have gone in before Travis because it had been a few hours since my shower. Embarrising...

So I am really tired and I have to pack and fold laundry...but instead of just doing it and getting it over with so I can sleep, I am procrastinating ( i have no idea if that is spelt right) I am such a dumbass. 

lobster tomorrow...mmm...can't wait...plus I get to see my daddy...YAH...I miss him so much. 

yah, i guess thats it, i got to get off my ass and get this shit done so I can sleep..well try to sleep...the man is playing halo...errr..i hate that shit.

So..a lot has gone on since my last update. Some life altering. Some just plain awesome. I start with all the good things first.

Went to that resort in New Hampshire. OMG. It was great. Fireplace, private balcony (we were the hightest up to so noone could see in) Jacuzzi..oh..grand.. And the adult onlt pool and hot tub was right outside close so we could go there, and there was barely anyone and no kids. So that was cool. And from our balcony there was a nice pretty field with trees, so it was private, and we looked to the right of our balcony and there was a fucking bear!! We saw it two nights in a row. That was cool too. We went shopping in North Conway which is a nice place, all kinds of neat shops, and then a bunch of outlet stores: Old Navy, Aeropostale, Nike, ADIDAS, Big Dogs, Nautica, Tommy Hilfiger...and the list goes on. So needless to say we came back broke. Shawn is so wonderful. He came up with going there, and paid for the room, and drove all the way there in back. I couldn't ask for a better man. God I love him.

Then on the fourth of July I got a call at 7 in the morning, dad was in the hospital having a heart attack. Talk about being scared shitless. We were at Shawns so it was an hour drive to the hospital. But Dad is doing good. It was a clogged artery and they put a stint into it. I am so scared. Even though its over and hes ok, i'm not completely ok. I am going to worry all the time now, I mean, I don't know how I could ever go on in my life if I lost my dad. He's only 41..he has a way to go and it could happen again..but he has quit smoking and drinking and is doing good with his diet..so thats good, but he is going back to work next week...I don't think he should be going back to were he is..its going to kill him..its Scary. 

Now back to a better note. This past weekend we went to Shawns Aunt and Uncles camp in Eastbrook. It was fun. Saw a parade and fireworks. And the best part of all was Amie and Travis finally met, and I believe they hit it off. They may just be a couple soon. Cross my fingers. They are both great people and they deserve to be happy like me and Shawn. Good luck to you two!!

I got a raise at work...51 cents so I am making $10.76 now. Definatly needed. I just made a budget and Shawn and I are starting a savings account to put money for his durango, and then out house into. money will be tight the next two weeks...but after that...we can save 500-1000 a month if we stick to this budget. 

Well I guess that is it for now. miss you guys..and leave me some damn comments, i get bored when shawns on Halo and need something to do..hehe..

HAPPY ONE YEAR ANNIVERSARY BABY......

 

So today is one year for me and Shawn....yah...I am so happy..

I wish I felt better though. Have had a bad tooth/earache, so I called in Monday, went to the dentist tuesday to get my tooth pulled...but they said they could save it, so the dug all the nasty decay out of it and put in a temporary filling. When he was drilling though...the novacain didn't work in the tooth...so i ended up feeling the intense pain and yelping out...ouch...then after the novacaine wore out it starting hurting worse than before I got it "fixed" and today I thought I was going to die..it wasn't even my toothache that hurt..its my ear...it has this intense sharp pain. So going to the docs today and hopfully get it all fixed before my big weekend.

I can't wait for this weekend, its going to be awesome...shopping in N. Conway, jacuzzi, swimming and lounging by the pool, just me and shawn, alone, together...how awesome is that...and so romantic. It feels so good to be with Shawn. Now I want to pass on this wonderful feeling to another friend...hopfully it works out between them. I think they will go good together. We'll see though.

Well off to the doctors now...I miss you all...leave me some comments!! Let me know whats going on with all of you!

So thought I'd write a little update. Work is going good. Just started my Animal Care 1 class today. 4 hour class for the next 6 fridays. WooHoo...but thats four hours I get paid to sit there and listen. Today I actually stayed awake even though I came in at 4:30 to work, then had to sit through that. So thats 6.5 hours of overtime so far this pay period. Hope I get more...need the $$. 

Ya so with the whole "Slutface" thing. Her name is Heather. And here is what happened. I got drunk, got pissed and told Shawn he couldn't e-mail her anymore and to tell her the same...finally after bawling forever Shawn did do this because he realized how bad it really hurt me. Then, the next day I felt bad, and so being the bigger person...just like Reanna knows me to be (damn..she knows me too well) I e-mailed Heather and told her she could talk/write to Shawn, that although I do feel a little uneasy, it wasn't fair to Shawn. So she told me that she did have feelings for Shawn but she loved her husband..ect..and then I guess she e-mailed Shawn and said that he was to not e-mail her anymore and that me and her were now "buds" LOL..how ironic...I guess I got what I wanted by being the bigger person. So take this as a lesson...that by being the bigger person it will pay off in the end. So ya, I think that is all my gossip for now...I LOVE SHAWN..he's a fucking god. How did I get so damn lucky...

OMG...I can't believe how hot it is..but I'm not complaining..better than that nasty wet cold rain.

So the other weekend I went to Cyclones, the bar in Southwest with Ericka and Reagan. It was fun. Got REALLY drunk...and got a free drink from this guy. I took it...drank it in like 5 minutes...if that...and got out of there. I am a taken woman you know. But it was fun. Then this weekend Shawn and I went to The Acadia Zoo. That was fun. Took all kinds of pics. The monkey's were adorable. I want a monkey so bad. Then Sunday went to see the fam. We all went to Les and Diane and went swimming in the pool and got a nice burn..that better turn into a nice tan. Hell Ya. 

Work is going great. Love it. Got 10 hours overtime comming in this weeks paycheck....Yes...I can't wait. Told Nick I'd take overtime anytime this week...or anyweek. 

So I need some opinions.... Here is the senerio. Say there is this couple..we will call them Jaycey and Jonathan. And Jonathan knows this Girl..we will call her Slutface. And Before Jaycey and Jonathan were a couple this slutface wanted Jonathan and would write him love letters...until her husband found out...(told you she was a slutface) Anyways...then While Jaycey and Jonathan were together she saw them together and knew they were together then slutface writes a text message to Jonathan saying how she still loves him. And know still knowing they are together is e-mailing him all the fucking time. Does Jaycey have a reason to be pissed? And doesn't she have the right to say that she doesn't want him to write to her and that he and needs to tell her to stop writing to him. I mean if it were just some friend that was a girl...Jaycey wouldn't mind..Actually he is still good friends and still talks and writes to his ex.g-friend. And I am fine with that...but this is different...she wants him and she IS going to try and get him...Out of pure respect for me he sould tell her to stop writing to him...and out of respect for her husband...whom use to be his friend...he shouldn't be writing to her either because I'm sure he wouldn't be ok with it since they aren't friends anymore because of this. So..what do you guys think...is Jaycey in the right?? God I wanna kill a bitch...

 please leave comments...I need some guidence.

So June 29th is Shawn and I's One Year Anniversary and he has booked us a Penthouse at a resort in the White mountains in New Hampshire. It has a jaccuzzi, a balcony, a fire place. Then there is a Indoor and outdoor pool with hottubs, nightly bondfires, and all kinds of activities...Sweet. If you want to see it the link is in Shawn's Profile: pochong81...check it out. 

So I guess that's it...

So I passed my test and am officially a "Production Tech" and Jackson Labs..woohoo. I was so nervous...but the test was easy. Tomorrow I will have no trainer....scary...although tomorrow wont be too bad because it's a day off for everyody...so just a few of us are going in for overtime on the holiday. I'll be making like $ 16 something an hour that day. Looking foward to that paycheck. I'm hoping I can get some more overtime this week too. We'll see. 

So this upcomming Friday I am finally going out to a bar. Ericka and Reagan from work are going out to the Cyclone in Southwest with me. It's suppose to be just the girl because they said the guys there will buy us free drinks...but I am hoping Shawn shows up...it would be fun...but we'll see if he does or not. 
Then Saturday I have Ericka's Bridal Shower. So a fun weekend ahead. Can't wait.

Well I guess thats really all for now. Just a quick update.

THIS WEATHER BLOWS NASTY SMELLY BALLS!! I am so sick of rain, thats all it's done for almost two months. It is so depressing. I just went and bought spring/summer clothes and I can't even wear them. And this weekend is a 3 day weekend for me and guess what suppose to rain from now until atleast Sunday. Fucking wonderful.

So I am 21 and have been since the middle of March and I still haven't been to a bar. I have no life. I mean i do..me and Shawn hang out on the weekends, and its fun...but I just want to get out and have more fun. All of my friends that are 21 are too busy for me or live forever away ;-( And the one friend that would go out to the bars with me is only 20...21 in August. Crap. I just miss having my friends around and doing things like in highschool. At least I have Shawn though. He is always there for me...well unless he's playing Halo. Hehe. I love you baby. I just feel like getting really drunk tonight...but unfortunatly I must work in the a.m. Learning a new thing so I can't call in. Not that I would anyways. I guess I am just depressed. I don't know why..me and Shawn are as great as ever so it's not that. I think I'm lonely...but not..I have Shawn...so not that kind of lonely...just not having any other friends around lonely. Does anyone even know what the hell I am talking about? Haha. I don't even know if I do.

Work is going good though. I really like my job and the weeks go by fast this week is 3 months that I have been there. I take my test on Friday then I am done training and officially on my own. Kind of scary yet exciting at the same time. I think I may be staying in the room I am in now...so that will be awesome if thats the case.

Well I guess thats it for now. I miss all of you guys so much....and I love you Shawn..thanks for always being there for me.

We had Over the hill stuff all over the place and I made her cake and wrote  "6 feet under the hill"

Oh and i love Shawn. This friday was sooo lonely without him.  I went to mom and dads by myself. It pathetic that I live with him and I miss him sooo much just one night away. He won this basketball tournament yesterday and his picture should be in the bar harbor newspaper. He played 7 games back to back then got a little 15 minute break I guess...then played two more. Poor guy was sooo sore yesterday. God I love him....
